<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A little boy suffered serious head and leg injuries after he was hit by a reversing car while playing in his driveway.</p>

<p>Emergency services were called to a home on Thomas Mitchell Drive, Killarney Vale, on the NSW Central Coast on Tuesday following reports a four-year-old boy had been struck by a car.  </p>

<p>Five NSW Ambulance crews responded to the incident, along with CareFlight’s Rapid Response Helicopter which landed in a nearby sports oval.</p>

<p>The boy was treated by CareFlight’s specialist doctor and critical care paramedics and underwent an ultrasound at the scene to examine his injuries.</p>

<p>CareFlight’s Rapid Response Helicopter was called to an incident in Killarney Vale (pictured) to treat a four-year-old boy who had been hit by a car</p>

<p>He was transported by road ambulance to John Hunter Hospital in Newcastle, where he remains in a serious but stable condition.</p>

<p>Police have launched an investigation into the circumstances surrounding the incident.</p>

<p>Anyone with information is urged to call Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.</p>

<p>The boy remains in John Hunter Hospital in a serious condition with head and leg injuries</p>

<p>Motorists are urged to be extra vigilant and keep a frequent lookout for young children during the school holidays.</p>

<p>At least one child is run over in the driveway of their home each week in Australia, according to KidSafe NSW.</p>

<p>Eight children are killed each year after being hit or run over by a vehicle at home and while another 60 are seriously injured.</p>

<p>Most children run over by a vehicle at home are aged under-5.</p>
